@inherits Custom.Hybrid.RazorTyped

<h1>LightSpeed External Data</h1>

<p>
  These tests demonstrate LightSpeed output caching with data that behaves like an external source.
  The source data is generated in AppCode, so it can change independently of the Razor output cache.
</p>

<ol>
  <li><code>Dependency Flush.cshtml</code> caches the page output and registers an explicit external dependency key.</li>
  <li><code>App Flush.cshtml</code> caches the page output without an explicit dependency and relies on the app-wide flush path.</li>
  <li><code>Diagnostics.cshtml</code> stays uncached and shows the current raw source snapshots.</li>
</ol>

<p>
  Typical sequence: open one of the cached pages, note the rendered timestamp and generation, regenerate the source only,
  verify the raw source changed but the cached render did not, then regenerate and flush to see the next page load update.
</p>
